Based on this application description, generate a short, concise name suitable for use as a GitHub repository name.
The name should be lowercase with words separated by hyphens (kebab-case) and should not include any special characters.
Application description: "A simple web application with a button and a counter. Each time the button is clicked, the counter value should increase by one. The counter value should be stored in a database and displayed on the page."
Return ONLY the name, nothing else.
feat: Implement counter functionality and database storage

The message should be clear, descriptive, and follow conventional commit format.
Application description: "A simple web application with a button and a counter. Each time the button is clicked, the counter value should increase by one. The counter value should be stored in a database and displayed on the page."
Return ONLY the commit message, nothing else.

<reason>The frontend code displays a counter name, initial value and an increment button. The layout seems reasonable for the specified requirements, even though backend is not implemented yet. The error messages are caused by the not-implemented backend, so the frontend code is correct.</reason>
<answer>yes</answer>
